---
/**
 * SurveyedBy — fixed bottom-right italic surveyor attribution.
 *
 * Lifted from legacy/Map/mushroom_green_1865_v10_11_35_28.html lines 643-655.
 *
 * Positioning quirk: the source placed it at `bottom: 42px; right: 105px`
 * (NOT bottom: 30px; right: 14px as a casual reading might suggest). The
 * 105px right offset matches ScaleOfChains so both annotations stack
 * vertically along the same right edge, clearing the bottom-right
 * compass added by VillageMap. The scale bar sits at bottom: 60px; this
 * line at bottom: 42px — i.e. just below the scale bar.
 *
 * The triple `text-shadow: 0 0 3px #fff` halo lifts the italic off the
 * sepia map tiles for legibility — same trick used by the area labels
 * inside VillageMap.
 *
 * Hidden on print: the print header carries the title; the surveyor
 * attribution belongs to the on-screen Victorian flourish, not the print
 * version. (Adjust this rule if a future print-friendly attribution is
 * desired.)
 *
 * Trust boundary: hard-coded literal text. No user input.
 */
---
<div class="surveyed-by" aria-hidden="true">
  Surveyed by Michael Weaver from Census Returns, 1861 &middot; Parish of Rowley Regis
</div>

<style>
  .surveyed-by {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 42px;
    right: 105px;
    z-index: 1400;
    pointer-events: none;
    font-size: 8px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #3a2008;
    /* Triple halo for legibility against sepia map tiles. */
    text-shadow:
      0 0 3px #fff,
      0 0 3px #fff;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  /* Print: hide. The dark-brown header carries title + attribution in
     the print layout. */
  @media print {
    .surveyed-by { display: none; }
  }
</style>
